1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,519
You think filming me...

2
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:03,280
making a fool of
myself is valuable, huh?

3
00:00:03,513 --> 00:00:04,673
How much can I sell it for?

4
00:00:05,799 --> 00:00:07,320
More than your tea leaves are worth.

5
00:00:07,919 --> 00:00:09,199
More than 8 million?

6
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:10,560
Then I should film some more.

7
00:00:11,119 --> 00:00:12,640
Your tea leaves are worth 8 million?

8
00:00:13,439 --> 00:00:14,696
I sold them to you this morning.

9
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:16,000
Letting you pocket a cool 200.

10
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:20,239
Don't you dare post this video.

11
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:22,560
You think I'd have the heart to?

12
00:00:25,559 --> 00:00:27,399
You've seen all my movies?

13
00:00:28,199 --> 00:00:29,199
Which?

14
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:33,960
Swipe through.

15
00:00:39,719 --> 00:00:40,920
I've seen some.

16
00:00:45,159 --> 00:00:46,359
Qingtian showed them to you?

17
00:00:46,759 --> 00:00:47,759
Mm-hmm.

18
00:00:48,719 --> 00:00:50,159
You saw the award-winning one too?

19
00:00:53,799 --> 00:00:55,959
Do you actors really get
into character when you film?

20
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:57,799
How could we act if we didn't?

21
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:01,760
How long does it take
to get out of character?

22
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:04,240
It depends.

23
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:06,079
Sometimes it's quick.

24
00:01:06,159 --> 00:01:07,400
Sometimes it takes a long time.

25
00:01:10,359 --> 00:01:12,318
When the acting is real, the
audience believes it's real too.

26
00:01:12,319 --> 00:01:13,200
No wonder there are still so many fans...

27
00:01:13,201 --> 00:01:14,841
shipping your CP from seven years ago.

28
00:01:16,439 --> 00:01:18,040
You know quite a lot, huh?

29
00:01:18,519 --> 00:01:19,759
Qingtian always talks about it.

30
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,560
You should stop growing tea.

31
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:25,840
Come down from the
mountain and be my assistant.

32
00:01:26,799 --> 00:01:28,040
Eight million a month.

33
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:31,079
A month? You've got some nerve.

34
00:01:32,573 --> 00:01:33,699
What would you have me do?

35
00:01:33,866 --> 00:01:36,053
Prepare tea, wash clothes, make food...

36
00:01:36,539 --> 00:01:38,919
prepare your luggage, hold your phone?

37
00:01:41,319 --> 00:01:42,920
It's not exactly skilled labor, is it?

38
00:01:45,006 --> 00:01:46,006
Aerial photography?

39
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:48,560
Well, I don't need you flying every day.

40
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:57,640
Driving, giving massages, handling some...

41
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,920
emergencies.

42
00:02:04,519 --> 00:02:06,519
You really are quite versatile.

43
00:02:08,439 --> 00:02:09,240
Right?

44
00:02:09,319 --> 00:02:10,840
Eight million is worth considering.

45
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,240
That's robbery!

46
00:02:21,439 --> 00:02:22,639
Robbing a celebrity.

47
00:02:23,159 --> 00:02:24,840
Anyway, I have a lot of your videos here.

48
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,159
What other videos?

49
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,639
I'm going to sleep.

50
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:34,120
I didn't sleep at all last night.

51
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,360
If you can't sleep, keep drinking.

52
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:48,200
"A Winter Sun Wakes the Wind in Spring Hills' Dream"

53
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:55,500
(Episode 2: Termite Mushroom)

54
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:58,400
I really have to talk about
my Baobao Maomao.

55
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,520
Lang Di's company is filming in Tianyi.

56
00:03:00,599 --> 00:03:04,240
The IP address of Lang Di's
last post was also in Tianyi.

57
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,239
After that, there was no...

58
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,000
leaked news of him leaving Tianyi.

59
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:11,240
Proving that Lang Di is still in Tianyi.

60
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:14,119
Haojue just showed up
in the comments section.

61
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:16,319
The IP also shows Tianyi.

62
00:03:18,039 --> 00:03:20,879
This means Baobao Maomao are together!

63
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,560
They're warming up for
the variety show in advance.

64
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,680
Sister Lan.

65
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,840
Sleeping?

66
00:03:43,199 --> 00:03:44,199
No.

67
00:03:45,159 --> 00:03:46,159
It was an accident.

68
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,320
What do you mean, an accident?

69
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:56,279
Shi Yuhao is going to make
a big deal out of this again.

70
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,199
Let me ask you.

71
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,640
Do you still have feelings for him?

72
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,360
No way.

73
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,160
Then why did you agree to be on the show?

74
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,400
I don't know why I agreed either.

75
00:04:07,319 --> 00:04:09,318
Brother Guo showed me
the proposal for the show.

76
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:11,000
I agreed without even thinking.

77
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,960
I guess I just wanted to
see what he was up to.

78
00:04:14,199 --> 00:04:16,375
But it's definitely not because
I still have feelings for him.

79
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:18,216
If you don't have feelings,
don't waste your energy on him.

80
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,720
I'll help you withdraw from the
show on the company's behalf.

81
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:21,959
No need, Sister Lan.

82
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:24,000
I want to handle this myself.

83
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,319
Lu, look over here! Lu!

84
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:11,000
Who's that? A new featured actor?

85
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,720
Lang Di's debut CP, Shi Yuhao.

86
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:15,560
Not as handsome as you.

87
00:05:24,759 --> 00:05:27,600
Sister Lan, I want to see Qinglang.

88
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,536
You can't just see him because you want to.

89
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:32,519
Shi Yuhao, have you no shame?

90
00:05:38,839 --> 00:05:40,040
He's not answering my calls.

91
00:05:40,519 --> 00:05:42,160
Even if he did, there's nothing to say.

92
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:46,639
What do you want to say to him?

93
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,240
We're about to be on the show together.

94
00:05:51,399 --> 00:05:52,479
So on the show...

95
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,720
we can't act like enemies, right?

96
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,518
I don't mean anything else by it.

97
00:05:57,519 --> 00:05:59,040
I just want to meet with him.

98
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,759
Spend a few days catching up.

99
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:04,080
You don't have to worry
about the show's ratings.

100
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:06,360
Since Qinglang chose to do this show...

101
00:06:06,519 --> 00:06:08,199
he'll take his work seriously.

102
00:06:08,319 --> 00:06:10,359
But he won't play along
with you to hype up the CP.

103
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,439
If that's all you're thinking about...

104
00:06:12,879 --> 00:06:14,479
I advise you to drop out of the show.

105
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,360
Sister Lan, there's no need to say that.

106
00:06:18,959 --> 00:06:20,438
If I wasn't trying to hype the CP...

107
00:06:20,439 --> 00:06:22,120
why would I invite him on the show?

108
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:28,959
That's right. I do need
him to make a comeback.

109
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,360
Yuhao.

110
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:34,439
I'm glad to see you being so honest now.

111
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:37,519
If you had this attitude seven years ago...

112
00:06:37,759 --> 00:06:40,399
daring to say what
you want and go after it...

113
00:06:40,639 --> 00:06:42,679
none of what happened
later would have occurred.

114
00:06:43,519 --> 00:06:46,120
If you had hyped up the
publicity with Qinglang back then...

115
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,960
you wouldn't be in this position now.

116
00:06:50,639 --> 00:06:53,120
Qinglang messaged you back
then, and you never replied.

117
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,360
Now you want him to pay attention to you?

118
00:06:55,759 --> 00:06:58,519
Shi Yuhao, the world
doesn't revolve around you.

119
00:06:59,759 --> 00:07:01,920
Don't think we don't know what you did.

120
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,536
That movie Qinglang was
trying to get back then...

121
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:07,200
if it weren't for your company
reporting him behind his back...

122
00:07:13,279 --> 00:07:15,720
It's a good thing he
didn't film that movie.

123
00:07:15,879 --> 00:07:17,319
He won an award for another one.

124
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,720
Sir, you need to move your car.

125
00:07:29,759 --> 00:07:31,399
I think this side here has collapsed.

126
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:33,935
The back of the head here.

127
00:07:33,959 --> 00:07:36,279
Hold on, let me lift the hair up first.

128
00:07:47,319 --> 00:07:48,319
Do you know him?

129
00:07:48,439 --> 00:07:49,439
No.

130
00:07:50,639 --> 00:07:51,919
You've never heard of Shi Yuhao?

131
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,439
Nope.

132
00:09:04,519 --> 00:09:05,519
Come out.

133
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,719
If you're going into the
mountains, you should have told me.

134
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,559
Following me secretly...

135
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,639
What if you got lost?

136
00:09:30,919 --> 00:09:32,319
There are bears in these mountains.

137
00:09:33,799 --> 00:09:34,799
Are they big?

138
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,840
I'm not kidding. There really are bears.

139
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:44,360
Termite mushrooms. Where did you find them?

140
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,960
So these are termite mushrooms.

141
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,798
I was just about to look them up online...

142
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:49,239
but I realized there's no signal.

143
00:09:49,279 --> 00:09:50,240
If you can't find any termite mushrooms...

144
00:09:50,241 --> 00:09:51,721
were you just going to keep hiding?

145
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,159
In front of you...

146
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,558
I already feel useless enough.

147
00:09:54,559 --> 00:09:56,199
I have to be useful for something, right?

148
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:00,080
You're eating it raw?

149
00:10:01,039 --> 00:10:02,439
Aren't you afraid of hallucinating?

150
00:10:02,559 --> 00:10:03,559
I am.

151
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,360
It smells so good.

152
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,680
Termite mushrooms are
the only kind you can eat raw.

153
00:10:19,039 --> 00:10:20,039
There are so many.

154
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:24,720
Then there must be more up ahead.

155
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,440
Hey, don't run off.

156
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:41,200
Last year, my friend in the capital
asked me to mail him some mushrooms.

157
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,279
He ended up getting food poisoning.

158
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,159
No hospital in the capital could cure him.

159
00:10:45,639 --> 00:10:47,759
He had to fly to Tianyi
to get the antidote.

160
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,720
Today, he asked me for mushrooms again.

161
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:52,039
I told him I could only
send termite mushrooms.

162
00:10:52,799 --> 00:10:55,439
But I only find a patch of termite
mushrooms once every two years.

163
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,000
That's it?

164
00:10:58,759 --> 00:11:00,039
You're so lucky.

165
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:02,216
Finding termite mushrooms on
your first trip into the mountains.

166
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,840
I dream about picking termite mushrooms.

167
00:11:03,919 --> 00:11:05,120
I'm obsessed with them.

168
00:11:09,559 --> 00:11:11,519
I've passed by that tree
a dozen times this year.

169
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,799
They only appear when I pass by.

170
00:11:19,559 --> 00:11:21,255
When termite mushrooms
break through the soil...

171
00:11:21,279 --> 00:11:23,079
mountain delicacies
can rival any seafood.

172
00:11:26,279 --> 00:11:27,439
I didn't say that.

173
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,600
A writer wrote it.

174
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,919
So you don't go to school?

175
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,920
You just come to the
mountains to work every day?

176
00:11:40,799 --> 00:11:42,519
The mountains are the best teacher.

177
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,240
How so?

178
00:11:45,799 --> 00:11:46,919
In books, they say...

179
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:48,518
if you find an injured bird...

180
00:11:48,519 --> 00:11:50,079
you should take it home and save it.

181
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:52,039
But in the mountains...

182
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,799
if you find an injured bird...

183
00:11:54,039 --> 00:11:56,720
letting it go is returning it to nature.

184
00:11:57,639 --> 00:11:58,960
I did an experiment once.

185
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,520
The bird I took home
died with its eyes open.

186
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,519
I left it in the forest.

187
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:05,239
The next day, I went to see it again.

188
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,559
And its eyes were closed.

189
00:12:08,279 --> 00:12:09,720
Another animal ate it.

190
00:12:14,159 --> 00:12:15,559
That's the law of nature.

191
00:12:16,799 --> 00:12:19,158
The mourning in rituals only belongs to...

192
00:12:19,159 --> 00:12:21,039
humans who think
they're so full of emotion.

193
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,399
Which writer wrote that?

194
00:12:25,799 --> 00:12:26,799
Xu Changyang.

195
00:12:27,159 --> 00:12:28,159
Pfft.

196
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:56,240
What's this?

197
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:57,720
Eat.

198
00:12:58,519 --> 00:12:59,519
Is it good?

199
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,440
I made this tea candy myself.

200
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,720
Why are you always so gloomy?

201
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,960
The character I'm playing
has this personality.

202
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:17,720
You're a method actor.

203
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:22,279
So, do you get aroused
when you film intimate scenes?

204
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,200
Changing sets!

205
00:13:27,039 --> 00:13:28,200
What are we shooting next?

206
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,320
Mwah, mwah, mwah.

207
00:13:31,919 --> 00:13:33,599
Actors, to the next set, quickly!

208
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:34,919
Coming. Let's go.

209
00:13:43,559 --> 00:13:45,319
After lunch, I'm heading
into the mountains.

210
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:50,320
Lunchtime!

211
00:13:58,120 --> 00:14:00,159
Is it okay if I post a
picture of you on Weibo?

212
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:01,919
When did you take this?

213
00:14:02,519 --> 00:14:03,559
While I was tailing you.

214
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:12,440
Go ahead. It's so blurry
you can't even tell who it is.

215
00:14:16,919 --> 00:14:19,200
Termite mushrooms!
Eating them all by yourselves?

216
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,639
Your brother found them.

217
00:14:20,919 --> 00:14:22,080
Then I've gotta have a bowl.

218
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:26,240
Changyang, take me to pick leaves
from that 200-year-old tea tree later.

219
00:14:26,559 --> 00:14:27,559
Sure.

220
00:14:30,519 --> 00:14:31,558
Have you eaten?

221
00:14:31,559 --> 00:14:32,639
Here to steal my food?

222
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:35,080
It's none of your business if I've eaten.

223
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,560
When are you going back to school?

224
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,600
None of your business
when I go back to school.

225
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,799
If I don't look out for you, who will?

226
00:14:47,159 --> 00:14:49,159
You have someone else
you should be looking after.

227
00:15:02,519 --> 00:15:03,960
Bro, are you going or not?

228
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,600
He's not going.

229
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:06,936
The sun's too strong during the day.

230
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:09,600
We'll come back later to pick
you up for Teacher Fu's house.

231
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:13,160
If you get hungry for lunch,
heat up the food yourself.

232
00:15:13,639 --> 00:15:14,720
I don't know how.

233
00:15:23,519 --> 00:15:24,559
You really don't know how?

234
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,840
I don't.

235
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:32,040
Then I'll heat it up for
you when I get back.

236
00:15:32,159 --> 00:15:33,600
I don't eat leftovers.

237
00:15:35,399 --> 00:15:36,959
I'll cook for you when I get back then.

238
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:43,279
Where's the drone
footage you shot yesterday?

239
00:15:43,639 --> 00:15:44,799
On my computer.

240
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,320
But my computer has a password.

241
00:15:46,759 --> 00:15:48,039
I'll show you when I'm back.

242
00:16:10,799 --> 00:16:11,600
Hello?

243
00:16:11,759 --> 00:16:14,240
Did Qingtian ever mention someone to you?

244
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:15,840
Who?

245
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,520
A tea farmer in the mountains.

246
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:21,080
He was always talking
to me about tea farmers.

247
00:16:21,919 --> 00:16:23,919
But did he ever mention
anyone in particular?

248
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,919
Like, describe them to you in detail?

249
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,600
Or even tell you their name?

250
00:16:29,519 --> 00:16:31,919
What's this about? Is Qingtian in love?

251
00:16:35,519 --> 00:16:36,600
No, not that.

252
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,559
He and I have never had the same taste.

253
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,639
Are you in love?

254
00:16:47,799 --> 00:16:48,799
I'm not either.

255
00:16:53,519 --> 00:16:54,519
Gotta go.

256
00:17:50,383 --> 00:17:52,229
[Voice note from Xu
the God of Wealth]

257
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:55,200
The person you're asking
about is Changyang, isn't it?

258
00:17:58,656 --> 00:18:00,183
[Now he's calling him]

259
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,400
You know Changyang?

260
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:06,720
We have the same last name.

261
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,160
Don't tell me he's your brother.

262
00:18:11,319 --> 00:18:12,319
He is.

263
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,240
No way. For real?

264
00:18:15,599 --> 00:18:17,880
I'm the one who introduced Qingtian to him.

265
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:23,880
Let me take a look.

266
00:18:24,119 --> 00:18:25,119
Alright, Qi Haoyu.

267
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,598
You bring Han Lu over here.

268
00:18:26,599 --> 00:18:27,119
Okay.

269
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:29,560
Then push him onto the bed
and roll around a couple of times.

270
00:18:29,599 --> 00:18:31,199
And then you have to go mwah, mwah, mwah.

271
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,399
Make the movements bigger.

272
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:33,039
Bigger movements.

273
00:18:33,039 --> 00:18:34,039
Two rolls, max.

274
00:18:34,599 --> 00:18:35,240
Yes, yes, good.

275
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:35,799
That's good, that's good.

276
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:37,000
Then over to the curtains.

277
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:39,358
Then push him against the window.

278
00:18:39,359 --> 00:18:40,519
Even bigger movements.

279
00:18:40,839 --> 00:18:42,318
A couple more mwah, mwahs.

280
00:18:42,319 --> 00:18:43,598
And... okay, good.

281
00:18:43,599 --> 00:18:44,599
Come on, back over here.

282
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:46,160
Over here, to the sofa.

283
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,119
Okay.

284
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,719
And here you can push him onto the sofa.

285
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,559
More mwah, mwah, mwah. Two more rounds.

286
00:18:50,759 --> 00:18:52,720
Keep going until the
director yells 'cut, ' okay?

287
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:53,559
Got it.

288
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:54,839
Hey, this blocking is good.

289
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:56,518
Hey, Brother Guo.

290
00:18:56,519 --> 00:18:59,118
Let's have the lighting
change from day to night.

291
00:18:59,119 --> 00:18:59,880
A little darker, okay?

292
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:00,720
Ah, okay, okay.

293
00:19:00,799 --> 00:19:03,758
Okay. Brother Dao, please
clear out these props.

294
00:19:03,759 --> 00:19:04,240
Clear them out.

295
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:04,759
You got it.

296
00:19:04,759 --> 00:19:05,400
Coming, coming.

297
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,400
Hey, okay.

298
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:17,838
Stop messing around.
This blocking is complicated.

299
00:19:17,839 --> 00:19:18,839
Have you memorized it?

300
00:19:19,039 --> 00:19:20,719
It's a piece of cake.

301
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:21,759
Yeah, right.

302
00:19:24,359 --> 00:19:26,199
Let your big bro walk
you through it. Come on.

303
00:19:28,559 --> 00:19:29,160
Hey, okay.

304
00:19:29,161 --> 00:19:30,358
Kiss him just like that in a minute, okay?

305
00:19:30,381 --> 00:19:31,581
All this kissing has me dazed.

306
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,200
Are we shooting every kissing
scene in the show today?

307
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,720
Looks like it, according to the call sheet.

308
00:20:01,699 --> 00:20:03,060
I'm fine with it.

309
00:20:03,359 --> 00:20:04,559
But can you handle it?

310
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,359
Aren't you a method actor?

311
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,160
If you bite me again,

312
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:13,599
I'll bite you right back.

313
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:18,720
Bring it on.

314
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:28,799
Let me touch up your makeup.

315
00:20:44,039 --> 00:20:46,000
Sister Jingjing, can you
cover this mark for me?

316
00:20:46,359 --> 00:20:47,039
Hey, Brother Guo.

317
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:48,719
Move that light a little more to the right.

318
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,720
Okay.

319
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:52,400
This side, this side, this side.

320
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:56,440
Hey, don't cover it. It looks good.

321
00:20:57,559 --> 00:20:58,799
Alright, director, roll camera.

322
00:21:11,359 --> 00:21:12,359
Qinglang.

323
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:47,799
Qinglang, open the door.

324
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,480
Let's just stick to seeing
each other on the variety show.

325
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:55,160
Some things need to
be discussed in private.

326
00:21:55,839 --> 00:21:57,919
I texted you a couple of
days ago, but you didn't reply.

327
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,519
But I know you saw it.

328
00:22:01,279 --> 00:22:02,359
I learned that from you.

329
00:22:02,559 --> 00:22:04,519
You never used to reply
to my messages either.

330
00:22:05,039 --> 00:22:07,039
You still remember something
from seven years ago?

331
00:22:12,036 --> 00:22:12,776
Shi Yuhao.

332
00:22:13,519 --> 00:22:15,200
Don't flatter yourself.

333
00:22:18,839 --> 00:22:19,839
Qinglang.

334
00:22:20,119 --> 00:22:21,880
I'm being serious this time.

335
00:22:24,039 --> 00:22:26,519
Maybe my timing was just off.

336
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:28,200
You're a top-tier star now.

337
00:22:28,359 --> 00:22:29,959
No matter what I say or do,

338
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,920
you'll think I have ulterior motives.

339
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:35,519
But I honestly don't have any other agenda.

340
00:22:37,119 --> 00:22:41,160
Back then... it was my fault.

341
00:22:41,839 --> 00:22:43,119
Sister Lan launched our careers.

342
00:22:43,519 --> 00:22:48,039
And I... stabbed you in the back.

343
00:22:48,519 --> 00:22:49,519
Who are you?

344
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:58,160
I'm looking for Qinglang.

345
00:22:59,119 --> 00:23:00,519
Do you have an appointment?

346
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,119
Who are you?

347
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,400
I'm his assistant.

348
00:23:16,279 --> 00:23:17,279
He's sleeping.

349
00:23:19,319 --> 00:23:20,959
You can talk to me if you need something.

350
00:23:22,519 --> 00:23:25,519
Are you the new assistant from his agency?

351
00:23:26,119 --> 00:23:27,119
Yes.

352
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:32,599
Then could you do me a favor?

353
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:33,798
Could you just tell him for me,

354
00:23:33,799 --> 00:23:34,440
to open the door?

355
00:23:34,441 --> 00:23:35,961
I need to talk to him about something.

356
00:23:36,039 --> 00:23:37,039
Okay.

357
00:23:41,039 --> 00:23:42,239
Open the door.

358
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,279
I'm home!

359
00:23:52,599 --> 00:23:53,719
Is your foot all better?

360
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:55,320
And you're already running around on it.

361
00:23:59,759 --> 00:24:01,000
What's that smell?

362
00:24:01,319 --> 00:24:03,240
Mountain dirt. I'm going to take a shower.

363
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:22,440
Delete it.

364
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:28,920
Who exactly are you?

365
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:31,880
I told you to delete the video.

366
00:24:32,759 --> 00:24:34,000
This is my house.

367
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:36,759
You're currently trespassing
and recording illegally.

368
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:38,399
Any video from inside this house...

369
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:39,720
if you dare post it online,

370
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:40,920
I'm calling the police.

371
00:24:43,319 --> 00:24:44,519
You can go now.

372
00:25:14,119 --> 00:25:15,359
How did I do?

373
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:16,640
Do I get a bonus?

374
00:25:17,319 --> 00:25:18,319
No problem.

375
00:26:48,559 --> 00:26:49,559
Cut!

376
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:51,519
Cut, cut, cut!

377
00:27:05,759 --> 00:27:07,295
We can't see anything under the covers.

378
00:27:07,319 --> 00:27:08,639
You don't have to do it for real.

379
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:12,880
Which one of us is doing it for real?

380
00:27:21,119 --> 00:27:23,160
Teacher Jingjing, I need a makeup touch-up.

381
00:28:02,559 --> 00:28:03,559
Smells delicious.

382
00:28:04,279 --> 00:28:06,119
Let's see if you still
have an appetite later.

383
00:28:14,036 --> 00:28:16,443
[Shi Yuhao is calling]

384
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,118
Let's meet.

385
00:28:20,119 --> 00:28:21,639
I'll be waiting for you on the bridge.

386
00:28:39,359 --> 00:28:40,359
Do you want some more food?

387
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,038
After hearing you say that,

388
00:29:19,039 --> 00:29:21,000
I finally understand
why I joined this show.

389
00:29:22,119 --> 00:29:23,720
A person lives on their pride.

390
00:29:23,839 --> 00:29:25,839
But they also hold grudges.

391
00:29:29,039 --> 00:29:31,880
I've mostly forgotten
what happened back then.

392
00:29:32,440 --> 00:29:34,559
But there's one thing I remember clearly.

393
00:29:34,799 --> 00:29:37,359
During that livestream, you
started to cut ties with me.

394
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,520
There was a game during the livestream.

395
00:29:39,559 --> 00:29:40,799
I fell.

396
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:43,039
You were standing right beside me.

397
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,240
You could've just bent
down and helped me up.

398
00:29:46,279 --> 00:29:47,880
But you took two steps back.

399
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,119
And watched me fall.

400
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:51,838
I was afraid you'd get heat for it.

401
00:29:51,839 --> 00:29:53,118
So I crawled forward on my own,

402
00:29:53,119 --> 00:29:54,160
and grabbed your leg.

403
00:29:56,079 --> 00:29:57,119
Fortunately,

404
00:29:57,480 --> 00:30:00,160
the stream froze for everyone
right as you backed away.

405
00:30:00,759 --> 00:30:02,960
All anyone saw was me grabbing your leg.

406
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:05,480
Shi Yuhao.

407
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:07,640
The way I see it,

408
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:09,416
unless there's some
deep-seated hatred within you,

409
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:11,079
anyone with a shred of human decency

410
00:30:11,119 --> 00:30:13,079
wouldn't just watch a
friend fall and do nothing.

411
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:18,599
It's been seven years. I really want
to know what you were thinking.

412
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,480
Why didn't you ask me back then?

413
00:30:23,559 --> 00:30:25,559
I messaged you back
then. Did you ever reply?

414
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:27,960
See for yourself.

415
00:30:29,359 --> 00:30:30,680
I've kept all the proof.

416
00:30:31,279 --> 00:30:32,358
Every time I got a new phone,

417
00:30:32,359 --> 00:30:35,240
I saved our entire chat history.

418
00:30:36,039 --> 00:30:37,358
You played blind,

419
00:30:37,359 --> 00:30:38,720
and forced me into silence.

420
00:30:39,279 --> 00:30:41,599
All these years, I've
been holding my tongue,

421
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:44,599
waiting for the day you'd be
standing in front of me, begging.

422
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:53,278
If it'll make you feel better,

423
00:30:53,279 --> 00:30:54,279
I'll do anything.

424
00:30:56,039 --> 00:30:57,039
Shi Yuhao.

425
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:59,960
You're so desperate for a comeback,
you'd even grovel like a dog.

426
00:31:00,279 --> 00:31:01,440
I've always been your dog.

427
00:31:01,559 --> 00:31:02,559
Enough.

428
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,080
The show's over. There's
no point in acting anymore.

429
00:31:12,759 --> 00:31:15,759
Two years ago, when I
gave my acceptance speech,

430
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:17,680
the first person I thought of was you.

431
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:21,960
Back then, I thought
I still cared about you.

432
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,720
But now I realize,

433
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,720
I should be thanking you.

434
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:29,640
Without you, I wouldn't have had
the spite to get me where I am today.

435
00:31:35,759 --> 00:31:37,759
I never thought you'd
resent me for so many years.

436
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:41,359
You know, I always thought...

437
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:42,798
We started our careers together.

438
00:31:42,799 --> 00:31:44,359
We shot our first series together.

439
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:48,839
Nothing could ever replace that.

440
00:31:50,559 --> 00:31:51,959
The moment you cut ties,

441
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:53,480
it was replaced by resentment.

442
00:31:57,359 --> 00:31:58,720
I'm not doing the variety show.

443
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:02,839
I just wanted to see you squirm in person.

444
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:07,680
I'll take responsibility
for breaking the contract.

445
00:32:08,359 --> 00:32:10,000
I know you can't afford the penalty.

446
00:32:14,799 --> 00:32:15,799
Let's go home.

447
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:19,799
Put your clothes on.

448
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:23,000
No. It's a hassle to take
them off again at home.

449
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:25,000
It's no hassle. I'll help you.

450
00:32:25,839 --> 00:32:27,839
You think it's a hassle
just to help me stand now?

451
00:32:28,599 --> 00:32:29,599
It's tiring.

452
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:23,559
You two are back. Where have you been?

453
00:33:28,263 --> 00:33:28,950
Come here.

454
00:33:37,279 --> 00:33:39,039
How many more days
are you staying in Molie?

455
00:33:40,559 --> 00:33:41,759
It's up to Changyang.

456
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:42,880
What?

457
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:45,680
My brother said how long
he stays here is all up to you.

458
00:33:46,839 --> 00:33:48,960
You're exactly the kind of
person who starts rumors.

459
00:33:50,119 --> 00:33:52,559
Alright, spit it out. What
do you want from me?

460
00:33:55,359 --> 00:33:57,199
A livestream. A charity
event to help farmers.

461
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:58,079
You don't make any money.

462
00:33:58,079 --> 00:33:59,079
And neither do I.

463
00:34:12,679 --> 00:34:13,679
Tian'er.

464
00:34:14,079 --> 00:34:14,880
Yeah?

465
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,920
You're running around busy every day.

466
00:34:17,239 --> 00:34:18,239
What for?

467
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:22,440
To survive.

468
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:29,800
Fine.

469
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:33,159
You can survive on my money.

470
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:47,000
When's the livestream?

471
00:34:47,679 --> 00:34:48,679
Is there a rundown?

472
00:34:49,159 --> 00:34:51,000
I was thinking of
scheduling it for the 19th.

473
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:52,760
That's when the Dragon
Elephant Festival begins.

474
00:34:52,761 --> 00:34:54,559
The air in the mountains will be cleaner.

475
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,360
How so?

476
00:34:58,360 --> 00:34:59,535
Meat is forbidden during
the Dragon Elephant Festival.

477
00:34:59,559 --> 00:35:00,839
Every household goes vegetarian.

478
00:35:01,679 --> 00:35:03,799
So the air will be free of
the smell of cooking meat.

479
00:35:04,159 --> 00:35:05,679
So I can't eat meat either?

480
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,000
Of course.

481
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:10,240
Changyang, make lots of
meat dishes these next two days.

482
00:35:12,559 --> 00:35:13,840
How about braised bear paws?

483
00:35:14,039 --> 00:35:15,400
I'll braise you!

484
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:26,480
Password?

485
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:35,679
Your password is my birthday?

486
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,639
Your birthday is pretty common.

487
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:41,760
It's on the desktop.

488
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:46,456
I'm just going to log into my
cloud drive on your computer.

489
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:47,480
Sure.

490
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:51,000
Don't delete the one where I threw up.

491
00:36:00,159 --> 00:36:03,480
Saving videos of people embarrassing
themselves is a weird hobby.

492
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:08,159
This is the most precious
footage of you in Molie.

493
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:10,639
It'll be a classic in a hundred years.

494
00:36:11,906 --> 00:36:13,386
Let me just rename the file.

495
00:36:13,436 --> 00:36:15,656
[Deleting the name "DJI Files"]

496
00:36:15,789 --> 00:36:20,749
[Feng Qinglang goes to
Molie Ancient Tea Village]

497
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:24,559
Screen Siren.

498
00:36:27,239 --> 00:36:28,000
Screen Siren.

499
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:29,000
Who's a screen siren?

500
00:36:35,679 --> 00:36:36,679
So young,

501
00:36:37,079 --> 00:36:38,359
what's going on in
that little head of yours?

502
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:39,360
Hmm?

503
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:44,559
Are you a screen siren or not?

504
00:36:44,639 --> 00:36:46,079
Are you? Are you? Huh?

505
00:36:57,203 --> 00:36:59,236
[Sister Lan calling]

506
00:37:02,079 --> 00:37:03,599
Check the message I sent you.

507
00:37:04,149 --> 00:37:07,969
[Notice that the variety show
production has been shut down]

508
00:37:14,639 --> 00:37:17,239
Someone reported you over that
movie you two did seven years ago.

509
00:37:17,559 --> 00:37:19,439
The higher-ups have shut
down the variety show.

510
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:21,976
Perfect. I was about to
announce I was quitting anyway.

511
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,240
This just saves me the trouble.

512
00:37:24,159 --> 00:37:25,920
You met with Shi Yuhao.

513
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:27,360
Yeah.

514
00:37:28,039 --> 00:37:30,800
Have you let go of the love and the hate?

515
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:32,960
Yes.

516
00:37:33,639 --> 00:37:35,960
The year I won the award,
I didn't even feel alive.

517
00:37:36,719 --> 00:37:39,760
Today, I truly feel like I'm living.

518
00:37:41,679 --> 00:37:44,199
There was a photo in the
Weibo post you made yesterday.

519
00:37:44,639 --> 00:37:45,960
Is that your new assistant?

520
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:47,920
He took me into the mountains.

521
00:37:47,921 --> 00:37:49,081
I just took a random picture.

522
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:52,200
Is there anything going on between you two?

523
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:57,840
Not at the moment.

524
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,280
I think the network cut out.

525
00:38:05,159 --> 00:38:06,159
Sister Lan.

526
00:38:06,599 --> 00:38:08,359
Qingtian wants me to
sell tea on a livestream.

527
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:09,680
It's a charity event for farmers.

528
00:38:10,360 --> 00:38:11,960
He already sent me the proposal.

529
00:38:12,719 --> 00:38:13,599
The company reviewed it.

530
00:38:13,599 --> 00:38:14,599
There are no issues.

531
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:16,480
Just cooperate with him and get it done.

532
00:38:17,039 --> 00:38:18,679
I'll have Jialin do your hair and makeup.

533
00:38:18,719 --> 00:38:19,400
Sister Lan.

534
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:20,280
He works fast.

535
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:21,479
Have you guys moved to the next location?

536
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,679
Tomorrow, we're moving
somewhere closer to Molie.

537
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:25,039
It's a half-day's journey.

538
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:27,600
I'll head over once
things are settled here.

539
00:38:27,679 --> 00:38:29,679
Sister Lan, I'll get the crew to clean up.

540
00:38:30,719 --> 00:38:31,840
It's no trouble at all.

541
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:35,440
Don't count on other people.

542
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:37,198
Are all of you coming?

543
00:38:37,199 --> 00:38:38,199
Yeah.

544
00:38:44,719 --> 00:38:45,719
Still awake?

545
00:38:46,039 --> 00:38:47,039
Going to bed now.

546
00:38:47,599 --> 00:38:48,799
Hey, let me throw that out.

547
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:49,800
Oh, no, it's fine.

548
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:03,280
Good night.

549
00:39:04,960 --> 00:39:05,960
Good night.

550
00:39:16,239 --> 00:39:17,879
Why do we look for bamboo worms at night?

551
00:39:18,639 --> 00:39:20,480
It's quiet at night, so you can hear them.

552
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:37,280
Give it to me. I'll chop.

553
00:39:41,039 --> 00:39:42,360
Am I chopping it right?

554
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:39,920
This is a little scary.

555
00:41:51,199 --> 00:41:52,199
Is it good?

556
00:41:53,719 --> 00:41:54,800
It's not bad.

557
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:58,000
We won't be able to eat this
during the Dragon Elephant Festival.

558
00:41:58,239 --> 00:41:59,239
That's right.

559
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,000
Let's find some more.

560
00:42:12,360 --> 00:42:13,360
Termite mushrooms.

561
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:14,960
What's wrong?

562
00:42:20,079 --> 00:42:21,840
There are more over here! Quick!

563
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:27,440
There are more.
